WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.060 --> 00:00:01.100
Love is a profoundly

00:00:01.100 --> 00:00:01.960
social emotion.

00:00:02.600 --> 00:00:03.540
At all stages of

00:00:03.560 --> 00:00:04.240
human development,

00:00:04.740 --> 00:00:05.139
love has

00:00:05.139 --> 00:00:05.919
in different forms

00:00:06.099 --> 00:00:06.839
been an integral

00:00:06.839 --> 00:00:07.719
part of culture.

00:00:08.359 --> 00:00:09.060
Love is not

00:00:09.060 --> 00:00:09.619
in the least

00:00:09.640 --> 00:00:10.599
a private matter

00:00:10.599 --> 00:00:11.619
concerning only the

00:00:11.619 --> 00:00:12.380
two loving persons.

00:00:12.919 --> 00:00:13.839
Love possesses a

00:00:13.960 --> 00:00:14.679
uniting element

00:00:14.679 --> 00:00:15.460
which is valuable

00:00:15.460 --> 00:00:16.300
to the collective.

00:00:22.460 --> 00:00:23.300
There's an almost

00:00:23.300 --> 00:00:24.679
natural tendency for humans

00:00:24.679 --> 00:00:25.460
to assume that

00:00:25.460 --> 00:00:26.719
ideas are eternal

00:00:26.719 --> 00:00:27.260
and that

00:00:27.260 --> 00:00:27.960
words have stable,

00:00:28.460 --> 00:00:29.239
unchanging referents.

00:00:29.660 --> 00:00:30.260
People have used

00:00:30.260 --> 00:00:31.339
the word 'love" for

00:00:31.339 --> 00:00:32.039
thousands of years,

00:00:32.640 --> 00:00:33.079
and so we

00:00:33.079 --> 00:00:34.159
assume naturally that

00:00:34.259 --> 00:00:35.100
there's one meaning

00:00:35.100 --> 00:00:36.179
underneath all these

00:00:36.179 --> 00:00:37.000
uses of love.

00:00:37.240 --> 00:00:38.079
Yet it's clear

00:00:38.079 --> 00:00:38.979
that the concept of

00:00:39.060 --> 00:00:40.060
love does change.

00:00:40.439 --> 00:00:41.460
In the 16th century,

00:00:41.700 --> 00:00:42.939
Machiavelli asked whether

00:00:42.939 --> 00:00:43.420
it was better

00:00:43.420 --> 00:00:44.659
to be
feared or loved.

00:00:44.920 --> 00:00:46.560
In the 2010s, several

00:00:46.560 --> 00:00:48.000
influential figures were saying

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:48.679
it was better to

00:00:48.719 --> 00:00:49.960
be respected than loved.

00:00:50.159 --> 00:00:51.039
Presently, I see

00:00:51.039 --> 00:00:51.899
people asking whether

00:00:51.899 --> 00:00:52.399
it is better

00:00:52.399 --> 00:00:52.740
to be

00:00:52.740 --> 00:00:53.899
loved or understood.

00:00:54.359 --> 00:00:54.920
Because someone

00:00:54.920 --> 00:00:55.700
can love you,

00:00:56.079 --> 00:00:56.859
but not understand

00:00:56.859 --> 00:00:57.579
you at all.

00:00:57.719 --> 00:00:58.439
While these questions

00:00:58.439 --> 00:00:59.740
are interesting in themselves,

00:01:00.079 --> 00:01:00.679
I think it's

00:01:00.679 --> 00:01:02.039
more fundamental and

00:01:02.039 --> 00:01:03.079
thus more interesting

00:01:03.079 --> 00:01:04.260
to observe that

00:01:04.260 --> 00:01:05.599
what people deem worthy

00:01:05.599 --> 00:01:06.359
of comparison

00:01:06.359 --> 00:01:07.319
to love changes.

00:01:07.659 --> 00:01:08.260
Now, it's not

00:01:08.260 --> 00:01:09.420
that love itself changes.

00:01:10.299 --> 00:01:10.840
There is no

00:01:10.840 --> 00:01:12.099
love in the abstract.

00:01:12.540 --> 00:01:13.519
Love, like any

00:01:13.519 --> 00:01:14.319
social phenomenon,

00:01:14.620 --> 00:01:15.319
is interpreted,

00:01:15.739 --> 00:01:16.219
and so we

00:01:16.219 --> 00:01:17.430
might wonder what interpretation

00:01:17.519 --> 00:01:18.680
currently makes sense.

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:20.159
What is so valuable

00:01:20.319 --> 00:01:20.920
such that it can

00:01:20.920 --> 00:01:21.959
rival the significance

00:01:21.980 --> 00:01:22.900
of being loved?

00:01:23.340 --> 00:01:25.200
That is a socio -historical question.

00:01:25.640 --> 00:01:26.439
Why do many view

00:01:26.439 --> 00:01:28.000
understanding as belonging to

00:01:28.019 --> 00:01:28.900
the core of love

00:01:29.120 --> 00:01:29.680
instead of other

00:01:29.680 --> 00:01:31.680
adjacent qualities like tolerance,

00:01:32.040 --> 00:01:32.959
patience, or justice?

00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:34.200
Addressing these

00:01:34.200 --> 00:01:35.299
questions give insight

00:01:35.299 --> 00:01:35.879
into current

00:01:35.879 --> 00:01:36.700
conceptions of love

00:01:36.840 --> 00:01:37.700
and our broader

00:01:37.700 --> 00:01:38.519
social structure.

00:01:38.819 --> 00:01:39.140
During the

00:01:39.140 --> 00:01:40.120
Russian Civil War,

00:01:40.299 --> 00:01:41.459
Alexandra Kollontai

00:01:41.459 --> 00:01:42.239
observed the lack

00:01:42.239 --> 00:01:43.280
of emotional depth

00:01:43.280 --> 00:01:43.840
and commitment

00:01:43.840 --> 00:01:45.099
the revolutionaries gave

00:01:45.099 --> 00:01:46.280
their romantic relationships.

00:01:46.879 --> 00:01:47.459
Not because the

00:01:47.579 --> 00:01:49.769
culture was particularly immature

00:01:49.780 --> 00:01:51.500
or because everyone had

00:01:51.500 --> 00:01:53.099
an avoidant attachment style.

00:01:53.319 --> 00:01:54.260
Rather, the material

00:01:54.260 --> 00:01:55.920
conditions of revolution made

00:01:55.920 --> 00:01:56.439
it so that

00:01:56.700 --> 00:01:57.400
people had no

00:01:57.680 --> 00:01:58.500
time or energy

00:01:58.799 --> 00:01:59.299
for the deep

00:01:59.459 --> 00:02:00.239
feelings that typically

00:02:00.519 --> 00:02:01.099
accompany love.

00:02:01.400 --> 00:02:02.140
Lying in bed

00:02:02.140 --> 00:02:03.180
for nights on end,

00:02:03.500 --> 00:02:04.400
unable to sleep

00:02:04.400 --> 00:02:05.239
as you yearn

00:02:05.239 --> 00:02:05.780
for your lover.

00:02:06.079 --> 00:02:06.780
That's a loss of

00:02:06.780 --> 00:02:07.700
energy and focus

00:02:07.700 --> 00:02:09.020
that revolution couldn't afford.

00:02:09.208 --> 00:02:10.900
"In face of the

00:02:10.900 --> 00:02:11.979
revolutionary threat,

00:02:12.379 --> 00:02:13.240
tender-winged Eros

00:02:13.240 --> 00:02:14.020
fled from the

00:02:14.120 --> 00:02:14.639
surface of life.

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:15.680
The fighting class

00:02:15.680 --> 00:02:16.259
could not have

00:02:16.360 --> 00:02:17.000
fallen under the

00:02:17.159 --> 00:02:18.280
power of winged Eros

00:02:18.659 --> 00:02:19.340
at a time when

00:02:19.340 --> 00:02:20.259
the clarion call

00:02:20.259 --> 00:02:21.699
of revolution was sounding."

00:02:21.919 --> 00:02:22.780
However, once the

00:02:22.780 --> 00:02:23.800
revolution succeeded

00:02:23.800 --> 00:02:24.979
and the Soviet Republic

00:02:24.979 --> 00:02:25.740
was established,

00:02:25.740 --> 00:02:27.699
Soviet situationships fell

00:02:27.699 --> 00:02:28.319
out of favor.

00:02:28.680 --> 00:02:29.219
People wanted

00:02:29.219 --> 00:02:29.939
something deeper,

00:02:30.280 --> 00:02:31.259
something longer lasting,

00:02:31.780 --> 00:02:32.539
because the material

00:02:32.539 --> 00:02:34.000
conditions allowed for that.

00:02:34.139 --> 00:02:35.180
The material conditions

00:02:35.180 --> 00:02:36.259
changed and so

00:02:36.259 --> 00:02:37.120
too did people's

00:02:37.159 --> 00:02:38.259
relationship with love.

00:02:38.699 --> 00:02:39.080
If we look

00:02:39.080 --> 00:02:40.599
at current material conditions,

00:02:41.080 --> 00:02:41.740
it makes sense

00:02:41.740 --> 00:02:43.139
why love and understanding

00:02:43.139 --> 00:02:43.840
are discussed together.

00:02:44.460 --> 00:02:44.819
I want to

00:02:44.819 --> 00:02:45.460
be clear that,

00:02:45.580 --> 00:02:46.319
of course, I

00:02:46.319 --> 00:02:47.580
don't think our historical

00:02:47.939 --> 00:02:49.240
epoch is unique in

00:02:49.240 --> 00:02:50.319
wanting to be understood.

00:02:50.319 --> 00:02:51.960
Everybody encounters a

00:02:51.960 --> 00:02:53.560
special and intimate psychological

00:02:53.560 --> 00:02:55.379
experience associated with

00:02:55.460 --> 00:02:56.439
what we call love.

00:02:56.699 --> 00:02:57.439
But the interpretation

00:02:57.439 --> 00:02:58.599
of that experience

00:02:58.599 --> 00:03:00.020
changes depending on

00:03:00.020 --> 00:03:00.819
the social context.

00:03:01.360 --> 00:03:02.419
Being respected may

00:03:02.419 --> 00:03:03.080
have felt like

00:03:03.080 --> 00:03:03.699
the right way

00:03:03.699 --> 00:03:04.680
to explain a

00:03:04.680 --> 00:03:06.379
special intimate feeling

00:03:06.379 --> 00:03:07.650
in the 1700s

00:03:08.099 --> 00:03:08.599
when respect

00:03:08.639 --> 00:03:09.340
was more rare.

00:03:09.639 --> 00:03:10.400
But in our modern

00:03:10.400 --> 00:03:11.500
pluralist society,

00:03:11.659 --> 00:03:12.460
respect is kind

00:03:12.460 --> 00:03:13.939
of a baseline expectation

00:03:13.939 --> 00:03:14.840
to be able to

00:03:14.840 --> 00:03:15.659
move through the world.

00:03:15.900 --> 00:03:16.400
So we have to

00:03:16.479 --> 00:03:17.620
consider the structure of

00:03:17.620 --> 00:03:19.300
current society to see

00:03:19.300 --> 00:03:21.199
why being understood is

00:03:21.199 --> 00:03:21.740
now the fitting

00:03:21.740 --> 00:03:23.080
term to interpret love.

00:03:23.360 --> 00:03:24.340
What makes understanding

00:03:24.340 --> 00:03:25.719
so special for personal

00:03:25.719 --> 00:03:26.919
relationships in a way

00:03:26.919 --> 00:03:28.240
that other virtues aren't?

00:03:28.699 --> 00:03:29.319
For one, the

00:03:29.319 --> 00:03:30.860
tremendous accessibility of

00:03:30.979 --> 00:03:31.960
products and services

00:03:31.960 --> 00:03:33.439
and the economic logic

00:03:33.439 --> 00:03:34.879
that mediates our relationships

00:03:34.879 --> 00:03:36.580
has devalued material

00:03:36.580 --> 00:03:37.919
instantiations of love.

00:03:38.379 --> 00:03:38.860
You don't need

00:03:38.860 --> 00:03:39.780
someone to burn

00:03:39.780 --> 00:03:40.639
CDs for you

00:03:40.639 --> 00:03:41.180
when you've got

00:03:41.180 --> 00:03:42.560
a cheap streaming service

00:03:42.560 --> 00:03:43.219
that can play

00:03:43.219 --> 00:03:43.860
any song you

00:03:43.860 --> 00:03:44.520
want at the touch

00:03:44.520 --> 00:03:45.020
of a button.

00:03:45.419 --> 00:03:46.259
Buying movie tickets

00:03:46.360 --> 00:03:47.219
for your partner loses

00:03:47.219 --> 00:03:48.099
value when you can

00:03:48.099 --> 00:03:49.319
watch anything at home.

00:03:49.599 --> 00:03:50.460
I'm not saying these

00:03:50.460 --> 00:03:51.979
acts aren't loving anymore.

00:03:52.259 --> 00:03:52.719
I would feel

00:03:52.719 --> 00:03:53.439
happy if someone

00:03:53.439 --> 00:03:54.250
made me mixtapes.

00:03:54.539 --> 00:03:55.219
But the social

00:03:55.219 --> 00:03:55.939
value of these

00:03:55.939 --> 00:03:56.800
acts has diminished.

00:03:57.139 --> 00:03:57.740
There are always

00:03:57.740 --> 00:03:59.479
convenient alternatives and

00:03:59.479 --> 00:04:00.180
we don't want

00:04:00.180 --> 00:04:00.719
love to be

00:04:00.719 --> 00:04:01.819
based in convenience.

00:04:02.219 --> 00:04:02.719
We might still

00:04:02.719 --> 00:04:03.659
want loved ones

00:04:03.659 --> 00:04:04.539
to do these material

00:04:04.759 --> 00:04:05.300
acts for us,

00:04:05.560 --> 00:04:05.939
but there is

00:04:05.939 --> 00:04:06.719
no need to

00:04:06.719 --> 00:04:07.340
rely on them.

00:04:07.680 --> 00:04:08.319
In fact, many

00:04:08.319 --> 00:04:08.860
think it is

00:04:08.860 --> 00:04:09.780
a virtue to be

00:04:09.780 --> 00:04:10.819
materially self-sufficient.

00:04:11.580 --> 00:04:13.039
Techno-capitalism nurtures

00:04:13.039 --> 00:04:14.280
isolated individuals,

00:04:14.639 --> 00:04:15.879
making others more obsolete.

00:04:16.420 --> 00:04:17.620
Under this system, it

00:04:17.620 --> 00:04:18.480
can feel like the

00:04:18.480 --> 00:04:19.680
only thing safe from

00:04:19.680 --> 00:04:22.240
obsolescence is our immaterial

00:04:22.240 --> 00:04:23.720
recognition of each other.

00:04:24.060 --> 00:04:24.939
How I understand

00:04:24.939 --> 00:04:26.360
you literally cannot

00:04:26.360 --> 00:04:27.699
be bought or possessed

00:04:27.699 --> 00:04:28.519
or reproduced.

00:04:28.899 --> 00:04:29.720
What matters then

00:04:29.860 --> 00:04:30.360
is not what

00:04:30.360 --> 00:04:31.160
our lover does,

00:04:31.680 --> 00:04:32.459
but whether what

00:04:32.459 --> 00:04:33.339
they do is

00:04:33.740 --> 00:04:34.680
responsive to US.

00:04:34.680 --> 00:04:35.500
This means the

00:04:35.500 --> 00:04:36.860
standard for what counts

00:04:36.860 --> 00:04:37.639
as being understood

00:04:37.639 --> 00:04:38.779
has also increased.

00:04:39.139 --> 00:04:39.879
The digital age

00:04:39.879 --> 00:04:41.180
makes it materially possible

00:04:41.279 --> 00:04:42.079
to know more about

00:04:42.079 --> 00:04:43.339
others than ever before.

00:04:43.600 --> 00:04:43.959
You can know

00:04:43.959 --> 00:04:44.660
someone you've never

00:04:44.660 --> 00:04:45.339
met just by

00:04:45.339 --> 00:04:46.379
stalking their various

00:04:46.379 --> 00:04:47.139
social media accounts,

00:04:47.579 --> 00:04:48.699
their likes and following.

00:04:49.040 --> 00:04:49.540
In the past,

00:04:50.019 --> 00:04:50.860
burning a perfect

00:04:50.860 --> 00:04:51.560
CD for your

00:04:51.560 --> 00:04:52.579
partner would require

00:04:52.579 --> 00:04:53.100
you to be

00:04:53.100 --> 00:04:54.240
attentive and present

00:04:54.240 --> 00:04:54.939
when you're together,

00:04:55.199 --> 00:04:55.579
so that you

00:04:55.579 --> 00:04:56.560
remember comments they

00:04:56.560 --> 00:04:57.360
make about music,

00:04:57.560 --> 00:04:58.420
or make complex

00:04:58.420 --> 00:04:59.860
inferences about their music

00:04:59.980 --> 00:05:00.639
taste based off

00:05:00.680 --> 00:05:01.680
of their general disposition.

00:05:02.019 --> 00:05:02.939
Now, if you

00:05:02.939 --> 00:05:03.439
want to burn

00:05:03.439 --> 00:05:04.139
someone a CD,

00:05:04.500 --> 00:05:05.019
you don't have

00:05:05.019 --> 00:05:06.019
to be that attentive

00:05:06.019 --> 00:05:06.720
when you're together.

00:05:07.000 --> 00:05:07.480
Even if you're

00:05:07.480 --> 00:05:08.060
on your phone

00:05:08.060 --> 00:05:08.800
half the time,

00:05:09.019 --> 00:05:09.439
you can always

00:05:09.439 --> 00:05:10.339
look at their Spotify

00:05:10.360 --> 00:05:11.540
listening history later,

00:05:11.980 --> 00:05:12.600
or check out their

00:05:12.600 --> 00:05:13.699
music highlights on Instagram.

00:05:14.139 --> 00:05:15.120
An act that once

00:05:15.120 --> 00:05:17.240
required emotional attunement can

00:05:17.240 --> 00:05:18.079
now be accomplished

00:05:18.079 --> 00:05:18.879
by an act

00:05:18.899 --> 00:05:19.560
of data collection.

00:05:20.259 --> 00:05:21.279
We also voluntarily

00:05:21.279 --> 00:05:22.300
hand out personal

00:05:22.300 --> 00:05:23.100
information for

00:05:23.220 --> 00:05:24.079
others to consume,

00:05:24.279 --> 00:05:24.720
posting our

00:05:24.720 --> 00:05:25.560
internal thoughts,

00:05:25.800 --> 00:05:26.759
photos of places we

00:05:26.759 --> 00:05:27.759
regularly frequent,

00:05:28.060 --> 00:05:29.120
clicking accept all

00:05:29.120 --> 00:05:29.899
to cookies which

00:05:29.959 --> 00:05:31.000
makes data brokers

00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:31.800
jump with glee.

00:05:32.560 --> 00:05:33.459
Target can literally

00:05:33.459 --> 00:05:33.899
know you're

00:05:33.899 --> 00:05:34.920
pregnant before your

00:05:34.920 --> 00:05:35.639
own family does.

00:05:36.180 --> 00:05:37.259
ChatGPT can give

00:05:37.259 --> 00:05:38.259
relationship advice

00:05:38.259 --> 00:05:39.160
tailored to your

00:05:39.160 --> 00:05:40.259
specific life details.

00:05:40.699 --> 00:05:41.319
It doesn't mean

00:05:41.319 --> 00:05:42.480
much to know things

00:05:42.480 --> 00:05:43.459
about people anymore.

00:05:43.800 --> 00:05:44.519
Knowing a lot of

00:05:44.519 --> 00:05:45.920
facts about someone might

00:05:45.920 --> 00:05:47.699
have constituted understanding

00:05:47.699 --> 00:05:48.519
in the past,

00:05:48.720 --> 00:05:49.379
but this is no

00:05:49.379 --> 00:05:50.199
longer sufficient.

00:05:50.540 --> 00:05:52.019
Otherwise, AI chatbots

00:05:52.060 --> 00:05:52.579
would seem to

00:05:53.139 --> 00:05:53.639
understand us.

00:05:54.019 --> 00:05:54.779
The standard for

00:05:54.779 --> 00:05:55.579
love must rise

00:05:55.579 --> 00:05:56.699
above what's ordinary.

00:05:56.980 --> 00:05:57.699
The standard for

00:05:57.699 --> 00:05:58.839
love must be special.

00:05:59.100 --> 00:05:59.720
Thus, to be

00:05:59.720 --> 00:06:00.360
loved is to

00:06:00.360 --> 00:06:01.740
be understood deeply,

00:06:02.120 --> 00:06:03.019
almost intuitively,

00:06:03.560 --> 00:06:03.959
as if to

00:06:03.959 --> 00:06:04.800
preserve a still

00:06:04.800 --> 00:06:06.120
uniquely human trait.

00:06:06.519 --> 00:06:07.279
I saw this TikTok

00:06:07.279 --> 00:06:08.079
where this creator

00:06:08.079 --> 00:06:09.339
tied Jean-Paul Sartre's

00:06:09.379 --> 00:06:11.639
concept of the Look to the intimacy

00:06:11.639 --> 00:06:12.699
of being understood.

00:06:12.959 --> 00:06:14.620
People say, I love

00:06:14.620 --> 00:06:15.360
you, when what

00:06:15.360 --> 00:06:16.180
they really mean is,

00:06:16.420 --> 00:06:16.980
I love the

00:06:17.259 --> 00:06:17.860
idea of you

00:06:17.860 --> 00:06:19.139
that I've already constructed

00:06:19.259 --> 00:06:19.759
in my head.

00:06:20.480 --> 00:06:21.879
That version is rarely

00:06:22.199 --> 00:06:23.019
